_data.text:
In both SMEs and Large Corporations, there are various types of activities happening simultaneously in the organizations. And some of them which are of great concern like Accounting, Inventory, Production, and many other activities. So to manage all these activities businesses, use numerous software solutions to run their entire organization's essential activities.

Likewise, while talking about the business activities, we discussed Accounting and Financial activities also. So for these two specific activities, many small and medium-sized businesses rely on Tally software solutions. Tally ERP (now Tally Prime) software is one of the best accounting software available in the Indian market.

Still, Tally Prime alone cannot solve all problems. Further, using much different software for different activities in the organization will create lots of extra work and confusion.

So to solve this problem, there is a solution that businesses can use one software for the activities in which Tally doesn't help, and for the rest Tally, is there. But there is one condition that the software must have a Tally Integration feature in it.

What is Software Integration?

So before talking about the Tally Integration, we must learn about Software Integration.

Software Integration is a process or practice of bringing different software or sub-software together and using them as a single software solution.

What is Tally Integration?

Now about the Tally Integration. It is also a software integration program that different other software products use. The software programs use it as a feature for transferring and coordinating data and other business activities on both of their platforms simultaneously. 

Why is there a need for using Tally Integration?

There are many reasons for using a different combination of software solutions like Tally and other products. And one reason for using the Integration software feature is to provide the best value for the investment done in particular software.

To survive in this business environment where there is a need for using different software for managing all of your daily business activities. There is a need for real-time visibility of data over all the software solutions which the company utilizes.

Further, the software has the use of sharing and communicating the updates to various departments in the organization. And sometimes, it also needs to get shared with external parties of the organization. So, in that case, the software integration helps the businesses.

Read more about - How Tally & TranZact together useful for SMEs.

Way Forward

So, to sum up, small businesses and companies that are using Tally software for their organization. If it is unable to solve all your problems. Then you must look for other software products for that particular issue.

Further, while choosing between the different software available in the market, you should opt for the one that is offering the Tally Integration feature to you. Because if you go for one customizable software solution, it will be expensive for your organization. And there may be a case many of your organizations can not use them. So to save you from this issue, you should go for a software solution that solves the issues which Tally is unable to solve. In this way, you can also utilize your investment and effort already made with Tally software. And to help you with that, TranZact is one such software that can solve your issues and provides the Tally Integration feature.

TranZact is a zero-effort Digital Transformation tool that helps digitize the entire business process right from Inquiry to Sales & Dispatch. Plus, it is very suitable for small businesses and manufacturing concerns.

The TranZact team provides their digitizing tool on a Freemium policy. And we are doing this to help our customers to take a step forward in digitizing their businesses without having to think over silly amounts of money.

So you all can go for TranZact or any other software only when it meets all their requirements. You all should check whether it is suitable for your business size and nature. And if the software satisfies all these conditions, like providing the Tally Integration feature. Then only should implement it in your organization.
